Author::::chiefwiley
DateTime::::2016-01-22T16:54:46Z
It is on the premium channel for nine months, and thereafter it will be available on the broadcast channel. There is likely not a single five year old who will know, or care, whether the show they are watching is on a paid channel or free channel, first run or re-run, new or twenty years old. The adults getting their undies in a bunch are the same people who get misty while an old Simon and Garfuncle album is playing, or settle down with beer and popcorn for a Gilligan's Island showathon. The term "false outrage" gets tossed about rather often in these sorts of circumstances, and the response often comes down to "think of the children!" It's the old class stratification by who gets first look game. My bet is if you actually asked the children, they wouldn't particularly care. These things only matter to those people normally expected to be the tolerant grow ups in the room. In the real world, the producers get enough resources to continue the show, and everybody ultimately gets to see both the old shoes and their modern counterparts.



